Roslyn has ten boxes. Five of the boxes contain pencils, four of the boxes contain pens, and two of the boxes contain both pens and pencils. The problem is to determine how many boxes contain neither pens nor pencils.The problem can be represented using a Venn diagram: egin{figure}[h]\centering egin{tikzpicture}\draw (0,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Pencils};\draw (2,0) circle (2cm) node [above] {Pens};
ode at (1,0) {$2$};
ode at (0.5,0.7) {$3$};
ode at (2.5,0.7) {$2$};\end{tikzpicture}\end{figure}
